Javins v. First Nat\u2019l Realty Corp.,.raw_text: Javins v. First Nat’l Realty Corp., 428 F.2d 1071, 1074–75 (D.C. Cir. 1970)
Javins v. First Nat\u2019l Realty Corp.,.proposition: See Restatement (Second) of Property: Landlord & Tenant § 5.1 (1977); Javins v. First Nat’l Realty Corp., 428 F.2d 1071, 1074–75 (D.C. Cir. 1970) (recognizing relationships between habitability, quiet enjoyment, and landlord obligation to control conditions of the premises and co-tenants); see also Massachusetts caselaw recognizing landlord obligations to abate substantial interferences with tenants’ possession and use by reason of other tenants or conditions within landlord’s control.

M.G.L. c. 186.proposition: Relevant statutory authorities include, without limitation, M.G.L. c. 186 (general landlord-tenant law), M.G.L. c. 239 (summary process provisions related to possession and enforcement), and M.G.L. c. 93A (unfair or deceptive practices where applicable).

M.G.L. c. 239.proposition: Relevant statutory authorities include, without limitation, M.G.L. c. 186 (general landlord-tenant law), M.G.L. c. 239 (summary process provisions related to possession and enforcement), and M.G.L. c. 93A (unfair or deceptive practices where applicable).

M.G.L. c. 93A.proposition: Relevant statutory authorities include, without limitation, M.G.L. c. 186 (general landlord-tenant law), M.G.L. c. 239 (summary process provisions related to possession and enforcement), and M.G.L. c. 93A (unfair or deceptive practices where applicable).
